import React from 'react';
import {
  View,
  Text,
  Button,
  Box,
  Stack,
  Divider,
  Image,
  AspectRatio,
  HStack,
  VStack,
  Center,
} from 'native-base';
import { MaterialCommunityIcons } from '@expo/vector-icons';

const Hero = ({ handleLogout }) => {
  return (
    <View>
      <VStack space={4} alignItems="center" height={'90%'}>
        <Button alignSelf="flex-end" left={0} top={0} variant="outline" onPress={handleLogout}>
          Logout
        </Button>
        <Center>
          <Box>
            <Image
              // @ts-ignore
              source={require('./assets/keeper.png')}
              width="150px"
              height="150px"
              alt="logo"
            />
          </Box>
        </Center>
        <Divider />
        <Center>
          <Text color="white" fontSize="lg">
            Welcome to Keeper ðŸ“¦ the storage Application
          </Text>
          <HStack>
            <Box bg="grey" p={3} m={10}>
              <MaterialCommunityIcons name="package" size={140} color="orange" />
              <Text fontSize="lg" color="white" bold textAlign="center">Find Storage</Text>
            </Box>
          </HStack>
        </Center>
      </VStack>
      {/* <keeper/> */}
    </View>
  );
};

export default Hero;
